<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>aoenla</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Senior Member<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Nov 1999<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Blah, this change is not for the better.  Just using regular archery (EQ/AM3) on xp mobs, I'm stealing aggro once/twice a fight.  Maybe that's ok, maybe that's as designed, although I might argue that in addition to all this new aggro, we really should have a jolt that lands a bit more reliably against the big mobs.  I can cast jolt over and over against many of the planar bosses, with no effect other than effectively slowing my attacks and draining my mana.<br />
<br />
If I use Trueshot, it's a guaranteed aggro steal, guaranteed summons, and likely death.<br />
<br />
This aggro change has effectively removed trueshot from our bag of tricks.  And a response of "just cycle your attacks during Trueshot" is not a good answer either, so don't even suggest it - trueshot is only 2 minutes duration every 72 minutes as it is.<br />
<br />
Blarg.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
