	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Hmm... I think this is going to depend on the situation.<br />
<br />
<br />
I used /disc Trueshot during a raid and didn't have to Jolt once. It can be noted that I was also using Guardian of the Forest, so was not casting any nuke spells. The duration of GOTF is pretty short so I don't nuke during it. It can also be noticed that I almost never /disc Trueshot on a mob unless it is a named and MT agro has been clearly established.<br />
<br />
<br />
In a regular exp group, the increased agro was more profound. Keep in mind that I didn't do any hard testing here. When I did straight archery, with no nuking I was ok for the most part. Even GOTF didn't cause problems. I wasn't snaring mobs unless they were low health and getting close to when they would try to run.<br />
<br />
When I used archery and nuked both, the SK who was tanking couldn't keep agro at all. The mobs invariably went after me. He had to work at it very hard to hold agro, and I had to hold back a lot.</p>
	
	
	
