	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Roophus Gunthar</b><br /><i>Well, this obviously means we aren't getting back our aa's because they would have done it with the hate nerf if anything.  So we are stuck with 45+ spent aa's toward archery.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>Seeing people say this is kind of getting repetetive and a bummer. =/<br />
<br />
Listen - The EQ Devs <b>DID NOT</b> do anything to nerf archery.  What they did do was change the way the agro system works <b>FOR EVERYONE AND EVERY CLASS</b>.  This change is not something that affects us alone, so they did not throw class specific refunds in AA points for those who spent it on archery AA.<br />
<br />
I'm not saying deal with it, live with it, or anything.  I'm just hoping you all get that point.  Just because they change the way the agro system works for everyone does not mean we should get our AAs back.  It affects everyone, not like the mana burn nerf or the mod rod nerf.<br />
<br />
I'm sure I'll be doing some form of PoP hunting or raiding some time soon, so I'll probably find this archery agro thing a problem soon enough tonight.  Last night I was in Vex Thal, though... didn't get to use archery much, but it seemed to work fine on one of the boss mobs.  But that's what people seem to be reporting anyway.  O.o</p>
	
	
	
