	<!-- message -->
	<p>We had VT last night and all 9 of our rangers were anxious to try out trueshot to see the changes first hand.  All but one of us went with trueshot after the ALL IN was called.  I had 15+ shots of 1800-2200 and started getting summoned about half way through.  I just backed up and kept shooting, no problems, the druid in our group kept me alive easily with a couple of heals.  The one ranger that did not use /disc until after the goo was down below 50% also got summoned about half way through his trueshot and died.<br />
<br />
On our second boss mob of the night, I waited about 1 min after starting my archery attack and cast two jolts that landed and went through trueshot easily with no summons.  Again, a ton of very high crits.  On that mob, I also went in for melee as we walled him after the rangers were done with trueshot.  I had no aggro and he never turned on me.<br />
<br />
From just my raid experience last night, the aggro is higher but it is not going to be instant death.</p>
	
	
	
