	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>We definitely need an improved jolt with this.  Or an evade skill at 65.  Rangers are very rogue-like and I do not see it as unfit to give a 65 ranger Evade.  I have often used sneak to get by see-invis mobs to pull corpses and whatnot.  I don't really think the rogues would begrudge us this.<br />
<br />
I will repost what I posted on a previous thread below regarding my findings.   What I'm seeing from posts is that it doesn't necessarily seem like aggro is based on actual dmg but POTENTIAL damage.  One ranger even posted he missed 2x, then got dodged and summoned.  In addition, several rangers are successfully trueshotting without summons, and others are jolting 20 times trueshotting and dieing instantly.  I think it would be beneficial for everyone who posts these findings to also post their ATK and bow they are using. <br />
<br />
Here are my results:<br />
My findings.  <br />
<br />
I use a bow of doom, swiftwind haste (plus same spell haste the tank has goin on, bard, chanter whatever's in group), and my ATK in these situations I was bard atk + my atk, so around high 1500s.  <br />
<br />
Was lucky enough to get into BoT group shortly after servers up.  Did 3 of the 4 nameds.  Trueshot on first one, gaukr summoned me halfway through.  I jolted a couple times, kept shooting fine until he got walled.  LOS not fixed.  Obviously no autoarchery.<br />
<br />
Later doing trials, got to prime executioner.  Popped on trueshot at the start of the fight (like I always did in the past, thinking the previous bot thing was a fluke).  . .    About 30-45 seconds later  I was summoned and the tank could not taunt it off of me.  I stayed up tanking for a good 30 seconds, too.  He couldn't do jack to get it off of me.  Wars need more cha items. <br />
<br />
Did trials again for another group shortly therafter and this time I did like old-school HoT raids.  I stayed back and tossed a couple quick heals on tank.  (this time i had jolt loaded, too).  Jolted a couple times then hit trueshot.  No aggro at all.  Not a single summon.  The tank does not have proccing weapons either.  I jolted once during trueshot.<br />
<br />
So this is doable ppl.  You just have to manage your aggro up front.  Don't wait until you're taking aggro to jolt.  That just screws up the tank with ping pong.</p>
	
	
	
