	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Odd that there seem to be differing experiences.  My experiences were crystal clear.  Perhaps it is gear or mob dependent.  To clarity my initial post then, I have the following data:<br />
<br />
EQ/AM3/Twisted Bow<br />
<br />
Targets:<br />
<br />
- on ST mobs leading up to MOTG and Prog, myself and the other ranger (similarly skilled/equipped) were getting summoned about once/fight..  Approximately 10 summons during, hrm, maybe 15 mobs?<br />
<br />
- on MOTG, I used Trueshot/GuardianOfForest1, was summoned about 30 seconds into my disc, I pingponged the mob for about 15 seconds trying to get away, MT regained aggro, I backed out and resumed what was left of my disc, bam got summoned again, and this time I just gave up and turned off attack and sat there spamming jolt trying to help the MT regain aggro.  He did, and I gave up archery and just turned on autoattack and used melee for the rest of the fight.  My dps that fight was 53 dps (I use EQCompanion), whereas my usual (depending on mob AC, etc) with melee is around 85, with regular archery about 120, and TS used to be much higher.<br />
<br />
- later, on Klandicar, I waited until MT aggro, waited another few seconds, then popped TS/GOF1.  I was positioned very distantly from Klandi.  Within about 15 seconds, I was summoned and slain outright.  I didn't bother looking at my dps on that one.  But I guess I did my part for the raid by absorbing 5 orange bubbles of ranger HPs worth of damage that the MT would have gotten had I not been summoned.  Yay me.  I'm a valuable addition to the raid.<br />
<br />
Maybe on the MOTG incident I can be accused of being caught unaware, but on Klandi I was as careful as I know how to be, short of not attacking at all.  So yes, only 2 data points, but pretty much identical results.  I'll do some more testing, I'll keep trying, but how many times do I have to say "Doc, it hurts when I do this" before I listen to his advice of "well then don't do that!"<br />
<br />
blarg</p>
	
	
	
	
	
